userStories.notes:
Files:
- plugins/jira/src/index.ts (add configSchema property and ConfigSchema import)
- plugins/jira/package.json (add configSchema to opentabs field)

Context:
Jira has both SaaS (atlassian.net) and self-hosted (Jira Server/Data Center) deployments. The plugin currently only supports the SaaS domain. Add optional instanceUrl so self-hosted users can configure their domain.

Current code in plugins/jira/src/index.ts:
```
import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';
...
class JiraPlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  readonly name = 'jira';
  readonly description = 'OpenTabs plugin for Jira';
  override readonly displayName = 'Jira';
  readonly urlPatterns = ['*://*.atlassian.net/*'];
  override readonly excludePatterns = ['*://*.atlassian.net/wiki/*'];
```

Changes:

1. In plugins/jira/src/index.ts:
   - Change `import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';` to `import type { ConfigSchema, ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';`
   - Add after the `excludePatterns` line:
     ```
     override readonly configSchema: ConfigSchema = {
       instanceUrl: {
         type: 'url' as const,
         label: 'Jira URL',
         description: 'The URL of your self-hosted Jira instance (e.g., https://jira.example.com). Leave empty to use Jira Cloud on atlassian.net.',
         required: false,
         placeholder: 'https://jira.example.com',
       },
     };
     ```

2. In plugins/jira/package.json, add to `opentabs` object:
   ```json
   "configSchema": {
     "instanceUrl": {
       "type": "url",
       "label": "Jira URL",
       "description": "The URL of your self-hosted Jira instance (e.g., https://jira.example.com). Leave empty to use Jira Cloud on atlassian.net.",
       "required": false,
       "placeholder": "https://jira.example.com"
     }
   }
   ```

Constraints:
- Do NOT remove or change existing urlPatterns or excludePatterns
- Do NOT set required: true
- Do NOT modify tool files, API files, or isReady logic
- The Jira plugin has `excludePatterns` for wiki/* — this must be preserved
